The paper proposes a deep learning framework for person search, which involves both pedestrian detection and person re-identification. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new loss function for training the network, which involves online instance matching, indicating that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also deals with large-scale datasets and involves image retrieval, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
